hort-worsens-2026-05-05-1221.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC copy book continues repairing and is close to the +$5M threshold, but not there. The improvement is also offset by aggressive ETH short expansion and persistent SOL zero-long/HYPE short pressure. This is not risk-on; it is BTC early repair against worsening cross-asset defensive positioning.\n\n**Decision:** Keep P1 **BTC early repair / below +$5M / cross-asset risk-off**. Do not treat +$3.79M BTC net as permission to loosen PM or HL. Require BTC net **+$5M**, then **+$10M** stability before risk-on discussion. Keep `ecb6` ETH/SOL/HYPE shorts as active veto context even as BTC short shrinks. Treat SOL **0L/7S** and ETH **-$26.54M** as strong defensive confirmation. Keep PM hours/filters unchanged and source canonical `[11, 12, 19, 20]`. Do not open outside hours. Keep YES-only / no-NO-trade behavior. Keep P4 **trend_risk_off / STOP** active. Keep HL live **notional_blocked**.\n\n**Next:** Watch whether BTC finally clears **+$5M** and whether that repair is confirmed by ETH/SOL relief. If BTC clears ",
